<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-772-720  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 772 720.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Oct 18 1989 n1287* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CDC takes on IBM 3090 with Cyber 2000, signs with MIPS. (ControlData Corp, MIPS Computer Systems Inc.)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Control Data Corp. (product introduction)MIPS Computer Systems Inc. (contracts).andO;Ticker:    CDA.andO;Product:   Control Data Cyber 2000 (Mainframe computer) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionMainframe ComputersContractsCooperative AgreementReduced-Instruction-Set Computers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>CDC TAKES ON IBM 3090 WITH CYBER 2000, SIGNS WITH MIPS...andM;Control Data Corp yesterday announced its white hope for the future, its newtop-end Cyber 2000 mainframe, and also revealed that it has joined thegrowing crowd cutting a path to the Sunnyvale, California door of MIPSComputer Systems Inc, signing an agreement for joint development of an&quot;applications-specific&quot; RISC-based computer.andP;  The new air-cooled ECL gatearray-based Cyber 2000 is rated at twice the power of the Cyber 990 and isdescribed as combining the attributes of a mainframe and a supercomputer: thechips are also claimed to be the densest ECL in the industry at 14,000 gatesper chip.andP;  The machine includes separate instruction and data caches withracy 5nS access times.andP;  Running the 100x100 Linpack benchmark, the Cyber 2000is claimed ;to perform at 30 MFLOPS against 38 MFLOPS for the Cray-2 on thesame benchmark.andP;  Claimed peak performance on the Cyber 2000 is 220 MFLOPS perprocessor, and the machine's channels run at 25 megabytes per second.andO;Offered in a 2000S scalar version upgradable to the 2000V vector model, themachine comes with one or two processors, and will ship late next year.andP;  Noprices were given.andP;  The company also announced the Disk Array Subsystem,which stores 32Gb and a transfer rate of 16.7Mbytes-per-second, usable withall its mainframes; the serial version ships in June, the parallel versionfourth quarter.andO;</TEXT></DOC>